endorse(address).details: Endorsed users are trusted contracts in the system. They are allowed to bypass         token restrictions (e.g. the Escrow can automatically receive tranche tokens by being endorsed), and         can automatically set operators in ERC-7540 vaults (e.g. the CentrifugeRouter) is always an operator.

executeScheduledRely(address).details: Can be triggered by anyone since the scheduling is protected

delay().notice: Returns the current timelock for adding new wards

deny(address).notice: Remove user as a ward (remove admin access)

denyContract(address,address).notice: Removes an address as a ward on any contract that Root is a ward on

endorsed(address).notice: Returns whether the user is endorsed

pause().notice: Pause any contracts that depend on `Root.paused()`

paused().notice: Returns whether the root is paused

rely(address).notice: Make user a ward (give them admin access)

schedule(address).notice: Returns when `relyTarget` has passed the timelock

unpause().notice: Unpause any contracts that depend on `Root.paused()`

wards(address).notice: Returns whether the target is a ward (has admin access)
